  "texts": [
    "We calculate the mean of the average precision for each perturbation and then term the fraction of perturbations with a q value below the significance threshold (0.05) as the fraction retrieved.",
    "Details about the computation of average precision and fraction retrieved are provided in the Methods section.",
    "In general, we find that the fraction retrieved for compounds is higher than that of genetic perturbations, across all conditions (Fig. 4a).",
    "This indicates that chemical compounds produce phenotypes that are more distinguishable from negative controls, compared with phenotypes produced by CRISPR knockout and ORF overexpression.",
    "We also find that the fraction retrieved is higher for CRISPR knockout than for ORF overexpression (Fig. 4a)."
  ],
